-- Happy-path traces for the platformer engine. Each trace points at
-- a small, hand-built test level under `test_levels/` rather than the
-- full game in `mario.ev` — production levels are too physics-noisy
-- for deterministic per-frame assertions, and the engine code is
-- exactly what we want to exercise anyway. Add a new test level when
-- you need a different scenario (jump arc, multi-platform pickup,
-- etc.) and point a new trace at it.

trace floor_coin_collected "programs/mario/test_levels/floor_coin.ev"
    -- Hero starts on floor at (60, 500). One coin at (200, 500).
    -- Run right; hero crosses coin around x∈(170, 218).
    key_down "Right"
    advance 1s =>
        coins[0].collected = true
        won = true
